The paper focuses on using deep learning techniques to classify and generate images of faces, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of novel approaches inspired by Gaussian mixture models and the handling of facial attributes suggest a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well. Additionally, the paper involves preprocessing steps and handling of images, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
